snippet.title: On Powerfully Managing your Career & Talent Mobility with Amber Beam
snippet.description:
Joining me on the seventh episode of the Sustainable Ambition Podcast is Amber Beam, a collaborator and fellow career coach who brings wisdom around managing your career over time, especially for mid-career changers.

Amber shares her concept around talent mobility, The Growth Effect, and is an advocate for employees and employers to get past old structures and norms to create more growth for both parties. Amber drops many wisdom bombs in this episode, including great advice on how to manage your career in your 20’s, 30’s and 40’s.

It's hard not to have a good time being in conversation with Amber, so I hope you appreciate her enthusiasm and encouragement to build a career with more flexibility and growth no matter your stage and age.

Thank you for sharing so many great insights, Amber! I loved being in conversation with you!

snippet.localized.title: On Powerfully Managing your Career & Talent Mobility with Amber Beam
snippet.localized.description:
Joining me on the seventh episode of the Sustainable Ambition Podcast is Amber Beam, a collaborator and fellow career coach who brings wisdom around managing your career over time, especially for mid-career changers.

Amber shares her concept around talent mobility, The Growth Effect, and is an advocate for employees and employers to get past old structures and norms to create more growth for both parties. Amber drops many wisdom bombs in this episode, including great advice on how to manage your career in your 20’s, 30’s and 40’s.

It's hard not to have a good time being in conversation with Amber, so I hope you appreciate her enthusiasm and encouragement to build a career with more flexibility and growth no matter your stage and age.

Thank you for sharing so many great insights, Amber! I loved being in conversation with you!

snippet.title: VOCÊ SABIA? Amber Riley reprovada no American Idol (leiam a descrição)
snippet.description:
Fazendo um adendo para não causar uma desinformação generalizada: na época em que fiz o vídeo, não deixei muito claro, mas a Amber não fez a audição para o Simon Cowell, mas audição para o AMERICAN IDOL, em que ele era jurado. Como dá pra ver no vídeo, eu não falo que ela cantou pra ele e ele deu não, mas que o programa a recusou, e esse programa é o mesmo que tinha, na época, o Simon. Só para vocês saberem, nem todos os cantores que participam vão direto para os jurados, alguns fazem algumas audições antes, sem os jurados que aparecem na TV. A Amber foi um desses casos. Desculpe se pareceu ourta coisa. Ainda assim, o fato dela poder cantar em outro programa, no qual o Simon, que também era jurado do programa que disse não para ela, estava presente, é um grande feito.

snippet.title: Amber Heard wears knitted vest at Cannes Film Festival
snippet.description: She was pictured keeping a low profile in a car with Heidi Klum's ex-boyfriend, art dealer, Vito Schnabel, on Tuesday. And Amber Heard, 32, appeared in high spirits as she headed onto a boat in Cannes at the 71st annual Film Festival on Thursday.She wore a knitted white vest top which was low-cut in design as she made her way down the promenade in 22 degree heat. The number was tucked into a pair of high-waisted baggy trousers as she walked along with her hands tucked into her pockets.    Share this article   Share  Her blonde locks were styled into loose curls as she battled a little wind as she neared the water. And she kindly posed for snaps with fans as she made the most of her day in the sunshine.   The night before, Amber wore a sensational gold knitted dress as she headed out in France, less than a day after being seen out with Vito, 31. The Rum Diaries actress, who last dated entrepreneur Elon Musk and was married to Johnny Depp before that was seen in a car with Vito in New York on Tuesday.The duo appeared deep in conversation while traveling somewhere in an SUV and ducked down out of sight after spotting onlookers. Schnabel dated America's Got Talent star Klum, 44, off and on from 2014 until 2017. Meanwhile, Amber's ex Elon Musk has a new lady in his life.The Tesla founder made things official with musician Grimes as they graced Monday night's Met Gala in NYC.

snippet.title: Penelope Cruz defends Johnny Depp amid Amber Heard legal drama
snippet.description:
Thanks for watching my video. 
If you like my videos, please subscribe to the channel to receive the latest videos 
  “I met Johnny when I was 19 years old,” said Cruz in the declaration, obtained by The Blast.  Cruz said that when they met, she only knew how to say two sentences in English: "How are you" and "I want to work with Johnny Depp." “Many years have passed and I have not only made three movies with him, but I also count on him as a great friend," she continued. "I’ve always been impressed by his kindness, his brilliant mind, his talent, and his peculiar sense of humor." Cruz and Depp, 56, have co-starred in the films “Blow,” “Pirates of the Caribbean: On Stranger Tides” and “Murder on the Orient Express." “I’ve seen Johnny in so many situations and he is always kind to everyone around. He is one of the most generous people I know,” she said, taking special note of his support during the filming of "Pirates," for which she was pregnant.  “During six months of my first pregnancy, I spent every single day with him while we shot ‘Pirates of the Caribbean.' My husband and I will never forget the sweetness, protection and kindness he treated me with during every single step of that process,” wrote Cruz. Cruz said that she and her husband, Javier Bardem, love Depp "very much" and that they "feel lucky to have someone so special in our lives." Cruz's declaration comes shortly after a similar one from Depp's former fiance Winona Ryder. Ryder, 48, said she found the domestic violence and abuse allegations against Depp "impossible to believe" and that Depp was not a violent person.  "I do not want to call anyone a liar but from my experience of Johnny, it is impossible to believe that such horrific allegations are true," she said in legal documents also obtained by The Blast. "I find it extremely upsetting knowing him as I do," Fox News' Jessica Napoli contributed to this report.

snippet.title: Talent Talk Interview   Amber Marshall
snippet.description:
Talent Talk is an online talk show, showcasing professionals in various aspects of arts and media including, film & television, music, cosplay, arts, etc. Shows are streamed live on the scheduled dates and are interactive for guests to ask questions during the show.

To find out more about Talent Talk see the links below.

Website: - https://www.talenttalkmedia.ca/
Faceboook - https://www.facebook.com/talenttalkmedia
Instagram - https://www.instagram.com/talenttalkmedia

Born and raised in London, Ontario, Amber Marshall trained at Lester B. Pearson School for the Arts, as well as The Original Kids Theatre Company in London. Amber has appeared in numerous film and television productions, displaying a remarkable range and vulnerability. She is most known for her work as Amy Fleming on CBC's long running series Heartland, now filming season 9.

Amber was awarded with the 2013 Fan Choice Award at the Canadian Screen awards and has kept an intimate relationship with her fans through communication on her Social Media pages. A strong actress, she has had regular roles in television series such as Super Rupert, The Power Strikers and Dark Oracle, and has guest appeared on different series, including Twice in a Lifetime and Doc. Heartland, a television series filmed in Alberta has been her dream come true. The contemporary family drama follows Marshall's character, Amy as she works with troubled horses and their owners to find harmony.

She has also played the daughter to Rob Lowe in a TV Classic Christmas tale called, "Christmas Shoes." To add to her Christmas TV Movie collection, Amber starred in Heartland's Christmas Movie, titled; "A Heartland Christmas." She also recently added the role of Nicole on a SyFy Channel Movie of the Week called Fallout Asylum to her resume.

A former veterinary assistant who is passionate about all animals, Amber has been around horses as long as she can remember. She has been riding since a very young age and says that the two things she loves the most - acting and horses - have come together to create this dream role of Amy on the Heartland series. Amber loves to be outdoors and enjoys overnight mountain trips with her horses and dogs. As Heartland films in Alberta, she has made a home for herself with her husband on a ranch outside of Calgary where she is surrounded by stunning vistas and of course, her animals.

snippet.title: Amber Heard is seen at JFK airport in New York
snippet.description: She's been busy promoting her role as Mera in the upcoming Aquaman movie.And Amber Heard didn't appear to be slowing down one bit as she was seen arriving at JFK Airport in New York Saturday.The star, 32, flattered her svelte figure in a pair of skinny jeans as she touched down in the Big Apple.This comes just after it was revealed that her ex-beau Elon Musk has moved on with another woman.The Tesla and SpaceX founder is reportedly dating Tyler Haney, who is the founder and CEO of athletic-apparel startup Outdoor Voices.A source told Page Six that Haney and Musk 'have been dating for a few weeks'.If Heard was bothered by the news, she didn't show it.Amber looked very fashionable during her airport outing.She accentuated her slim figure with a braided leather belt.Tying the look together, the Texas-born talent donned a Western hat and a studded purse at her side while wearing pointy patent leather shoes with a single buckle.Further adding to her accessories, the actress put on a copper pendant necklace, silver earrings and round sunglasses.Heard kept her hair down, looking naturally tousled, also keeping her face makeup free.The ex of Johnny Depp also carried a sizable leather purse stuffed with things for the trip.While making her way out of the airport, the Magic Mike XXL actress reached over her head to check her hat before getting into her ride.On Friday the star was in LA, where she attended a benefit for the Syrian American Medical Society.Amber's been dedicated to the plight of Syrian refugees.Her work with the Syrian American Medical Society took her to Zaatari Refugee Camp in Jordan last month, where she spent time with people fleeing violence in their home country.And before that Heard was in Las Vegas promoting her upcoming blockbuster Aquaman, which comes out December 21.This year will also see the release of her film London Fields and the star has three other projects in the pipeline beyond 2018.

snippet.description: Si Amber Heard accuse Johnny Depp d'avoir été violent envers elle, les amis de ce dernier n'y croient pas. En pleine bataille judiciaire contre son ex-épouse, l'acteur star de Pirates des Caraïbes peut compter sur le soutien indéfectible de ses proches.
